Remarks: The observation of Ax (1952) that there is only one plate-like structure instead of two ( Graff, 1905 ), surrounding the tubiform stylet, can be confirmed. This plate has a spine-like projection at its distal end, which lies close to the stylet but is displaced in highly squeezed animals ( Fig. 7E
1
). The bursal appendage is short ( Graff, 1913 24 Mm; Ax, 1952: 20– 21 Mm), barrel-shaped and consists of nine, maybe ten, short tubes ( Fig. 7E
3
).

